        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>GENERAL</title>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The 26-SI series self-rectifying alternator (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0801801">Figure 1</hotlnk>and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0801802">Figure 2</hotlnk>) is a brushless unit featuring a built-in voltage
                        regulator.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0801801" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0801801" filename="../figg08/G0801801.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>26-SI Series Alternator</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f0801802" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0801802" filename="../figg08/G0801802.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Sectional View of Alternator</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. GREASE RESERVOIR</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. STATIONARY FIELD COIL</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. FAN</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. PULLEY</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. SEALED BALL BEARING</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. ROLLER BEARING</callout1>
                            <callout1>7. RECTIFIERS</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The only movable part in the assembly is the rotor, which is mounted on a ball bearing at the
                        drive end, and a roller bearing at the rectifier end. All current-carrying conductors are
                        stationary. These conductors are the field winding, the stator windings, the six rectifying
                        diodes, and the regulator circuit components. The regulator and diodes are enclosed in a sealed
                        compartment.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>A fan located on the drive end provides air flow for cooling. An extra large lubricant
                        reservoir for the rectifier-end frame bearing contains an adequate supply of lubricant. The
                        drive-end frame has a permanently sealed lubricated ball bearing. No periodic maintenance of any
                        kind is required.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>An "R" terminal is provided on all units to operate auxiliary equipment.</para>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
